[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 17   [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **L110** — TODO (TechWriter): Expert review V3 / L6 (LOW). Specify time-zone discipline in harmonization: store collection_ts as a UTC instant in the harmonized record. Preserve the source-system local-time string in a separate source_local_ts field if needed for display, but all temporal ordering, baseline-window computation, and trend-duration calculation use the UTC instant. This avoids ordering bugs in multi-site health systems where labs are collected across time zones.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 18   [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **L164** — TODO (TechWriter): Expert review A2 / H3 (HIGH). Promote baseline-reset event handling from the production-gaps prose to a first-class architectural primitive: (1) a maintained baseline-reset event feed (medication starts, therapy transitions, major procedures, new diagnoses) sourced from the EHR's medication, problem, and procedure feeds; (2) baseline computation that excludes values prior to the most recent applicable reset event for each (patient, LOINC) pair, falling back to "insufficient_history" during the post-reset stabilization window; (3) a scheduled change-point detection backstop (Bayesian online change-point or PELT) that emits candidate reset events when a statistically significant level shift is detected; (4) DynamoDB record carrying baseline_reset_events metadata; (5) CloudWatch metric on baseline_resets_per_patient_per_year with anomaly alarms. This is the per-patient longitudinal-pipeline correctness primitive that separates this recipe from the volumetric forecasting recipes earlier in the chapter.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 19   [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **L315** — TODO (TechWriter): Expert review A3 / M2 (MEDIUM). Specify the idempotency contract for Step 5: (1) generated_at_ts is computed once at the pipeline-start step and propagated through Step Functions state, not recomputed per Lambda invocation; (2) add a CURRENT#<loinc_code> sort-key value per (patient_id, loinc_code) pointing to the latest surfaced trend, with a conditional write ConditionExpression: attribute_not_exists(generated_at_ts) OR generated_at_ts < :new_generated_at_ts; (3) the EventBridge trigger uses a pipeline_run_id derived from the schedule invocation ID so at-least-once delivery produces idempotent runs; (4) BatchWriteItem retry on UnprocessedItems is bounded (5 retries) and emits a metric on unprocessed count; (5) backfill writes from baseline-reset reconciliation use a revision attribute and the CURRENT conditional-write logic; (6) the suppressed-trends S3 write is keyed by (date, patient_id, loinc_code, pipeline_run_id) so reruns overwrite cleanly.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 20   [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **L317** — TODO (TechWriter): Expert review S3 / L1 (LOW). Add a sentence to "Clinical Consumers" or to the AWS Implementation noting that the surfaced-trend payload is PHI in the strongest sense (patient identifier plus dated lab values plus clinical interpretation), and every downstream consumer (CDS Hooks responder, inbox aggregator, population-health dashboard) inherits the PHI posture and must be a HIPAA-eligible service or a BAA-covered first-party application. The boundary at the DynamoDB serving table is not a PHI-to-non-PHI transition.
