[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 22   [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **L404** — TODO (TechWriter): Expert review A6 / M5 (MEDIUM). Promote medication-and-intervention awareness from production-gaps prose to an architectural primitive: (1) a maintained feed from EHR medication and procedure systems, ingested via FHIR MedicationRequest and Procedure resources into HealthLake; (2) a per-LOINC configuration that maps LOINC codes to relevant medications and procedures (e.g., creatinine to ACE inhibitor, ARB, contrast agent; hemoglobin to ESA, iron supplementation, transfusion); (3) the trend-detection step optionally takes the medication-and-intervention context as a feature input; (4) the clinical-relevance step optionally suppresses or down-weights trends temporally adjacent to a relevant medication start or procedure; (5) the surfaced-trend payload includes the medication-and-intervention context that was considered, so the clinician sees the system is aware of e.g. the ACE inhibitor start three months ago. Per the recipe's own framing, this is the single most important production refinement.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 23   [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **L408** — TODO (TechWriter): Expert review A7 / M6 (MEDIUM). Add an optional "Panel-Level Aggregation" architectural step between the per-LOINC clinical-relevance step and the clinical-consumers delivery: a Lambda that consumes per-LOINC surfaced trends, groups them by clinically-defined panels (kidney function = creatinine + eGFR + BUN + electrolytes; liver function = AST + ALT + ALP + bilirubin), and applies panel-level rules. The architecture should show this as an optional step that defaults off in the basic pipeline and can be enabled per panel as the deployment matures.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 24   [0m:[38;5;9m[49m - **L414** — TODO (TechWriter): Expert review A8 / M7 (MEDIUM). Add a CDS Hooks responder to the architecture (API Gateway + Lambda, both VPC-deployed and behind WAF) wired to the DynamoDB serving table. The Lambda implements the CDS Hooks specification, queries DynamoDB by patient_id on the patient-view hook, formats the surfaced trends as CDS Hooks cards, and returns them with appropriate severity-band styling. Show this path in the architecture diagram; the EHR's CDS Hooks client connects to the API Gateway endpoint over a HIPAA-eligible mutual-TLS or signed-JWT channel.
